{
  "texts": [
    "While fully grounding an LLM in the human sense may not be feasible, there could be value in partially grounded systems for specific applications.",
    "Such systems might integrate some form of sensorimotor learning or interaction, albeit limited, to enhance their utility in certain tasks.",
    "However, this should not be misconstrued as equivalent to modeling human cognitive capacity or passing T3.",
    "The pursuit of AI systems that can pass a T3 Turing Test or model human cognitive capacity in its entirety requires a focus on more than just linguistic capabilities.",
    "It necessitates a foundational rethinking of how AI systems are developed, moving beyond language processing to incorporate genuine sensorimotor experiences and learning."
  ]
}